consent_form: I certify that I am the legal parent (biological/ adoptive) and I hereby give my consent to be a subject in this research.
collect_freelist_1: Rocks - over the years, if we go somewhere either special like the Grand Canyon or to the creek down the street, she has picked these up; as she has grown, this collection continues.
collect_freelist_2: Dolls - specifically American Girl dolls; she has a few of her own and has worked with my father to showcase them by making them individual "bedrooms" on bookshelves
collect_freelist_3: Pressed Pennies - when we visit Disney World she has collected these as a souvenir
collection_origin_1: She picks them up on her own and brings them home; a few friends have given her some after she shared this at a show and tell in school.
activities_1: Other than putting them in a box she has, she does not do much. Occasionally, she has painted some of them like the ones she gets on hikes.
collection_reason_1: I think she has liked the feel of them and how some are different as well as how they appear differently while sitting right next to others. I think it is something that can also remind of places we've been.
collection_origin_2: Receiving as gifts from family in terms of the specific doll but her creating of bedrooms the items she gathers to add to their bedrooms are things she either makes like wallpaper by coloring/designing paper or sewing bedding with her grandmother.
activities_2: With the dolls specifically, she dresses and arranges them but with the bedroom set up, she switches around how it looks by making decorations out of paper or other items around the house as well as had made beds with her grandparents by cutting foam and making bedding with them (pillows, blankets)
collection_reason_2: She likes home design and I think the bedrooms she has created give her an outlet to design the space and change it for her dolls; I think she likes the size of the dolls because they are bigger than a Barbie and she can clothe them, do their hair, etc. Her collection started with my American Girl doll that I gave her.
collection_origin_3: If we go to Disney World, she is allowed to spend a certain amount of money and can decide to purchase these.
activities_3: Other than reviewing and organizing in a booklet, she doesn't do anything.
collection_reason_3: Her aunt works at Disney so she has been many times and this is something she can get on each visit that doesn't cost too much so within her limit. She doesn't really interact with this collection except when we are going away to Disney World or upon our return. I think she also enjoys 'hunting' for the machines when we are there and what new images she can find.
